<font class="pn-normal">    First off, this only applies to open raids (organize guild systems such as DKP will solve this problem). Secondly, no one likes to lose pp/items, everyone makes sacrifices in a raid (time, pp, etc). You have the ultimate choice of joining/leaving the raid, not to mention you chose the class. Ive never see anyone criticize extensively about reagants. I play a 65 necro, and hey I lose a peridot per pet summoned (plus more with coffins/EEs) and its not fun but its our duty. Do we have to lose an extra hour or two in the raid just to sort out loot to the 10 clerics, 6 necros, and 4 mages? (in this case its up to the raid leader, although many players are busy) Ultimately, we &lt;&lt;ALL&gt;&gt; benefit from loot/flags with the teamwork we put in (not because of some greed from the certain player).<br>
<br>
&lt;&lt;If reagants are a major concern to you or anybody else, id advise not attending the raid (there are certainly more of the class out there) or consider making another character. &gt;&gt; =)</font>
